BT 1 0 0 1 0 75 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Paper 104 derived T_c = 337K from the mean-field critical temperature \(4812K\) times the Ginzburg correction factor for) Tj T* (frustrated networks \(0.07\), giving 2% accuracy. This paper presents a second, independent derivation using cooperative) Tj T* (hydrogen bond percolation on the diamond \(tetrahedral\) lattice. Result: T_c = 333K \(1% from measured 330K\), with ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (zero) Tj T* (free parameters) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( -- all inputs are measured quantities. The derivation: the cooperative triad condition \(p_coop = p^3\)) Tj T* (applied to the diamond lattice bond percolation threshold \(p_c = 0.388, Grassberger 2003\) gives T_c where the spanning) Tj T* (cooperative H-bond network first percolates. Both derivations confirm T_c = 330K; this one is tighter and requires no) Tj T* (estimated corrections.) Tj T* ET
